<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-18T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-18T09:00:00-05:00" n="498" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/249: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Child</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-18T15:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">April 18,
                                        1922—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 19—1:34
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>60. Department’s number 50, April 15, 2 p.m. Foreign Office states that
                            no more deliveries will be made under contracts before or after joint
                            declaration.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Child</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>